@* THE OTHER BOUNDARY of decision 146: displaying a Random itself. C# renders "System.Random" (the
   type name); a JS object would render "[object Object]" -- a silent wrong render, section 10's
   forbidden mode. Valid Blazor; deliberately refused at the SLOT. *@

<p><span id="out">@rng</span></p>

<button id="go" @onclick="Go">go</button>

@code {
    private System.Random rng = new System.Random(7);
    private int n = 0;

    private void Go()
    {
        n = rng.Next(3);
    }
}
